#JamiesTogether #cookbook

node.text: Introducing @bighas___  even though he forgot to open his eyes this young boy is an incredibly talented cook! never judge a book by its cover bearing in mind I’m 6 foot tall Has has got to be in the 6ft 6 this lovely huggable lad is one of hundreds of my graduates from the legacy of Fifteen Restaurant and he truly cooks some of the most elegant real food I’ve tasted… there is no pretension with Has he tells it like it is but his heart and passion is food❤️ he doesn’t muck about he cooks on fire he eats with gusto but the heart of his cooking is both rustic and delicate and light of touch a gift it takes quite a long Time to learn tonight I’m supporting this lovely boy do his first supper club at the Jamie Oliver HQ it sold out in one hour… the restaurant industry has had a devastating year my intention is to support young talent do some incredibly exciting food in a collection of supper clubs celebrating the seasons my dream also is to bring back Fifteen.2 in a different way to help amazing young talent open their own small neighbourhood restaurants if you like this idea let me know in the comments box below as this is what makes me truly happy and if you fancy coming keep your eyes peeled for now good luck @bighas___ I believe in you ! have a wonderful two days cooking at my home I know you’re going to smash it! And give him a follow
Who needs some help with dinners or lunches for the rest of the week? Tag someone to share the inspo with. All the recipes & loads more over on my website. #dinnertime #dinnerideas

Shoutout to all you lovely lot getting involved in the 1st month of my cookbook club. This is just some of the amazing cook-ups that have been shared this month in the group!! Blown away by the cook-ups. I've loved seeing loads of you get stuck into @loveleluu's cookbook, sharing photos, chatting swaps, and being open to trying new recipes. SO good
If you love cookbooks, come and join our Facebook group if you haven't already! I've dropped the link in my bio and keep an eye out to see which cookbook we're diving into next month! Big Love JO x #jamieolivercookbookclub #cookbooks

Making fresh ravioli is not as scary as people think and you don’t need any fancy kit. The principle recipe here is 100g flour to 3 egg yolks per portion, so it’s really easy to scale it up or down. These little beauties freeze really well, so cook up a batch and stash them in a freezer, then all you need to do is drop the frozen ravioli in boiling water and cook until tender and piping hot. So delicious! Happy F R I D A Y lovely lot x
Full recipe in my bio - give it a go jox
